            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-320-person2199">
                  SARAH 
                  LUCAS
               <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2199" type="surname" value="LUCAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2199" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2199" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18170917-320-viclabel1636" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-320-victim2198 t18170917-320-viclabel1636"></join>, and live with my mother at Islington. On the 21st of August, I was returning from the Play about twelve o'clock at night - I missed the party that was with me. I met one of the prisoners in Drury-lane, and asked her the way to the city; she was leaving me, when the other prisoner came up, and persuaded me to go home with her into Charles-street. I went to bed there; when I got up the two prisoners were there. I asked them where my things were? I missed the articles stated in the indictment. They said I had no more than what was in the chair when they met me, and that my things were unpinned, as if I had been with some person, which was not the case. As I went out, the young woman in the next room asked me if I had lost any thing? I told her I had. She went with me to Bow-street, and got an officer, who took them into custody. My apron and petticoat were found on one of the prisoners, and the stays on the other, they were wearing them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-320-person2200">
                  MARY 
                  HARDY
               <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2200" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2200" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2200" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the next room to the prisoners. I heard them bring the prosecutrix home between twelve and one o'clock. I heard Ingram say she would have Lucas's stays-Steel said they would have the petticoat between them. Next morning I heard Steel tell Lucas to go home. She inquired for her things-Steel told her that her things were unpinned when they met her. Lucas told me what she had lost,</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-320-person2201">
                  JOHN 
                  TOWNSEND
               <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2201" type="surname" value="TOWNSEND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2201" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-person2201" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 22d of August, the prosecutrix and Hardy fetched me to Charles-street. I followed the prisoners into the room. I asked Steel what she had got in her apron? she said it was her petticoat-the prosecutor claimed it. I asked where the other things were? (they whispered to each other.) Ingram pulled the stays off; Steel went to the bed, and fetched the stockings and other things.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>INGRAM'S Defence. Barker brought the prosecutrix in, very much intoxicated. She said she had no money to pay for her lodging, and we must pledge her things. As we were going to pledge them the officer took us.</p>
               <p>STEEL'S Defence. She gave us them to pledge.</p>
               <p>INGRAM. - <rs id="t18170917-320-verdict1637" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-verdict1637" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 17.</p>
               <p>STEEL. - <rs id="t18170917-320-verdict1638" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18170917-320-verdict1638" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
